data.title: Fanfare (film)
data.meta_description: Fanfare is a 1958 Dutch comedy film directed by Bert Haanstra. The film was entered into the 1959 Cannes Film Festival and the 1st Moscow International Film Festival. It was the most successful Dutch film at the time with over 2.6 million admission until surpassed by the 1973 film Turkish Delight.
data.text: Fanfare is a 1958 Dutch comedy film directed by Bert Haanstra. The film was entered into the 1959 Cannes Film Festival[2] and the 1st Moscow International Film Festival.[3] It was the most successful Dutch film at the time with over 2.6 million admission until surpassed by the 1973 film Turkish Delight.[1]
